UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1366
1 AN ACT relating to eminent domain.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 416.670 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) Development shall be started on any property which has been acquired through
5 condemnation, for the purpose for which it was condemned, within a period of
6 eight (8) years from the date of the deed to the condemnor or the date on which the
7 condemnor took possession, whichever is earlier[, for the purpose for which it was
8 condemned. The failure of the condemnor to so begin development shall entitle the
9 current landowner to repurchase the property at the price the condemnor paid to the
10 landowner for the property. The current owner of the land from which the
11 condemned land was taken may reacquire the land as aforementioned].
12 (2) Subsection (3) of this section shall apply to:
13 (a) Any property for which the condemnor[ who] fails to:
14 1. Develop after acquiring[property acquired] by condemnation; or
15 2. [who fails to ]Begin design on highway projects pursuant to KRS
16 Chapter 177 within a period of eight (8) years after acquisition; or[,]
17 (b) Any remaining property that was acquired through condemnation for a
18 highway project pursuant to KRS Chapter 177 and was not used after the
19 completion of the project.
20 (3) The current landowner of any property described in subsection (2) of this section
21 is entitled to repurchase the property at the price the condemnor paid to the
22 landowner for the property.
23 (4) The condemnor shall notify the current landowner of the provisions of[ subsection
24 (1) of] this section. If the current landowner refuses to purchase property described
25 in this section, public notice shall be given in a manner prescribed in KRS Chapter
26 424 within thirty (30) days of the refusal, and the property shall be sold at auction.
27 [Provided, however, that ]This section shall not apply to property acquired for
